    "body": "`gen_help_html.lua` problem at: https://neovim.io/doc/user/usr_01.html Generated at 2026-05-06 19:58 from 7b00f58 \n\nuse_01.txt has the following valid modeline\n\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/9174157f7498bb79c51164d94aeaef6ce7508410/runtime/doc/usr_01.txt#L114\n\nbut it does not match against the regexps\n\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/9174157f7498bb79c51164d94aeaef6ce7508410/src/gen/gen_help_html.lua#L235-L238\n\nconsequently the web page has the modeline:\n\n> Next chapter: [usr_02.txt](https://neovim.io/doc/user/usr_02/#usr_02.txt)  The first steps in Vim\n>\n> Copyright: see [manual-copyright](https://neovim.io/doc/user/usr_01/#manual-copyright)  vim:tw=78:ts=8:noet:ft=help:norl:\n\nRegexps need to be updated, or\n```diff\n--- a/runtime/doc/usr_01.txt\n+++ b/runtime/doc/usr_01.txt\n@@ -111,4 +111,5 @@ donate part of the profit to help AIDS victims in Uganda.  See |Kuwasha|.\n\n Next chapter: |usr_02.txt|  The first steps in Vim\n\n-Copyright: see |manual-copyright|  vim:tw=78:ts=8:noet:ft=help:norl:\n+Copyright: see |manual-copyright|\n+vim:tw=78:ts=8:noet:ft=help:norl:\n```",
